comments: Bey (ATL) brings his arm toward George's (LAC) front, causing George to momentarily lose control of the ball before he immediately regains control.
Young (ATL) briefly grasps George's (LAC) arm, and the contact during the drive is marginal.
Coffey (LAC) is stepping forward with his right leg slightly extended when the ball ricochets off of him.
Coffey (LAC) contests Murray's (ATL) jump shot, and the contact after the release and follow-through is marginal.
Westbrook (LAC) is already in Murray's (ATL) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Young (ATL) briefly grasps Harden's (LAC) leg and immediately releases him as he corrects.
Young (ATL) steps forward into Harden's (LAC) lower body and initiates contact as he contests the jump shot attempt.
George (LAC) initiates contact to Young's (ATL) front which affects his SQBR during the drive.
Young (ATL) commits a take foul on Westbrook (LAC).
Replay review of the foul called on Bey (ATL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Bey (ATL) grabs and pulls Leonard's (LAC) jersey away from his body as Leonard passes the ball.
Leonard (LAC) is moving alongside Young's (ATL) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Harden (LAC) initiates contact with Bey's (ATL) head during his shot near the rim.
Johnson (ATL) commits a take foul on Coffey (LAC).
Westbrook (LAC) cleanly dislodges the ball from Okongwu (ATL) as they pursue the rebound.  Any ensuing arm contact after the dislodge is considered incidental.
Westbrook (LAC) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to the Hawks.
Westbrook (LAC) and Okongwu (ATL) briefly engage and disengage during the inbound.
Coffey (LAC) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to the Hawks.
Young (ATL) is bracing for the contact from Coffey (LAC) and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the contact.
Okongwu (ATL) cleanly dislodges the ball from Leonard (LAC) as they pursue the rebound.
George (LAC) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds.  Possession is correctly awarded to the Hawks.
Bogdanovic (ATL) moves along George's (LAC) path and marginal body contact occurs as the two come together at the same spot on the perimeter.
Young (ATL) commits a take foul on Harden (LAC).
Bey (ATL) makes contact with the ball, and with the part of Harden's (LAC) hand that is on the ball, as Harden secures the rebound.
